' Data-flow Diagram 08 — Justifications → neglect detection.
'
' Shows how block.justifications traverse the DAG to compute
' neglectedInvalidJustification.  This is the data-flow underlying
' the Level-2 (neglected-equivocation) and the NeglectedInvalidBlock
' validation paths.
'
' Source of truth for Figure 8.2 in slashing-specification.md.
'
' Render:
'   plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/slashing/diagrams/08-dataflow-justifications-to-neglect.puml

@startuml 08-dataflow-justifications-to-neglect
!theme plain

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor     #333333
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #BBDEFB
  BorderColor     #1565C0
}
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title Data-flow: justifications → neglected-invalid-block detection

' Edge color legend:
'   blue   (#1565C0) = read / extract from inputs
'   gray   (#546E7A) = predicate computation
'   green  (#2E7D32) = accept (block admitted)
'   red    (#C62828) = reject (block rejected as invalid)

artifact "block b\n(under validation)"             as B    #FFE0B2
component "VG: validation guard —\nreject duplicate-validator\njustifications (Bug #16 / T-9.15;\nInv_AcceptedProjectionCardinality)"  as VG   #FFECB3
artifact "b.justifications\n(input field of b;\nseq of {validator,\n latestBlockHash})\n— validated; one entry per validator" as J    #FFF8E1
database "CasperSnapshot.dag\n(pre-loaded DAG view\npassed alongside b)" as S    #BBDEFB

component "filter:\nlookup(j.latestBlockHash)\nexists ∧ block.invalid"  as F1   #FFECB3
component "AIE: authorized\ninvalid-block evidence index\n(post-fix Bug #14 / T-LivenessGap;\ndeploy_epoch_matches_target)"  as AIE  #FFECB3
component "exists:\nbonds(b).find(_.validator\n  == j.validator).stake > 0" as F2 #FFECB3
component "scan b.body.system_deploys\nfor SystemDeployData::Slash\n(post-fix only)"  as F3   #FFECB3

component "detector (Bug #11 / T-9.11):\ndetectable(view) ≜\n  detected_hash_seen(view)\n  ∨ |distinct_child_hashes(view)| ≥ 2\n(missing pointers contribute ∅;\nduplicate paths to one child collapse\nbefore cardinality is checked)"  as DET  #FFECB3

artifact "invalidJustifications"        as IJ   #FFF8E1
artifact "neglectedInvalidJustification\n: Bool"  as N    #FFE0B2
artifact "has_slash_system_deploys\n: Bool (post-fix)"  as HS   #FFE0B2

component "decision:\nif neglected ∧ ¬hasSlash\nthen Reject\nelse Accept"  as DEC  #D1C4E9

artifact "Right(ValidBlock::Valid)"                       as OK   #C8E6C9
artifact "Left(InvalidBlock::\nNeglectedInvalidBlock)"     as REJ  #FFCDD2

B  -[#1565C0]-> VG : input field access
VG -[#546E7A]-> J  : projection cardinality OK\n(one cited hash per validator)
J  -[#1565C0]-> F1
S  -[#1565C0]-> AIE : authorised\ninvalid-block index
AIE -[#546E7A]-> F1 : invalid-block candidates
S  -[#1565C0]-> F1 : s.dag.lookup(j.latestBlockHash)
F1 -[#546E7A]-> IJ
IJ -[#546E7A]-> F2
F2 -[#546E7A]-> DET : projected justification view
DET -[#546E7A]-> N
B  -[#1565C0]-> F3
F3 -[#546E7A]-> HS
N  -[#546E7A]-> DEC
HS -[#546E7A]-> DEC
DEC -[#2E7D32]-> OK    : Accept
DEC -[#C62828]-> REJ   : Reject

note right of DEC
  Pre-fix Scala: rejection fires
  whenever neglected = TRUE,
  even if b carries a SlashDeploy
  for the offender.

  Post-fix Rust + bug fix #9 (T-9.9):
  rejection requires
    neglected ∧ ¬has_slash_system_deploys
  i.e. self-correcting blocks pass.

  Source: validate.rs:1025-1027
  ("if neglected_invalid_justification &&
    !has_slash_system_deploys").
end note

@enduml
